         "q": "List the signs of lobar pneumonia.",
         "a": "Ill, anxious, restless, toxic, cyanosed child; tachycardia, dyspnoea, tachypnoea; central trachea with diminished chest expansion over the affected lobe; dull percussion notes; increased tactile and vocal fremitus on the affected side; diminished then bronchial breath sounds, later replaced by crepitations."
