         "a": "Lobar: homogenous, usually bacterial, dull percussion, increased fremitus, bronchial breathing, pleuritic pain present. Bronchopneumonia: patchy, usually viral, resonant equal percussion, crepitations, chest pain unusual. Trachea is central in both."
