         "q": "CLINICAL — How do you manage a suspected empyema?",
         "a": "Chest X-ray and ultrasound to confirm and assess loculation; diagnostic and therapeutic thoracocentesis with fluid sent for microscopy, culture, Gram stain, protein, glucose and cytology; drainage; escalate antibiotics per culture; and consider TB."
