         "q": "List the complications of catheterisation during exchange transfusion.",
         "a": "Gut perforation and peritonitis; wrong position of the catheter tip (which may excite cardiac arrhythmia if in the right atrium); necrotising enterocolitis; and liver cirrhosis as a long-term complication."
